subsection.p:
On the unit circle C:\quad x=\cos t,\qquad y=\sin t,\qquad 0\le t\le2\pi, we have dx=-\sin t\,dt,\qquad dy=\cos t\,dt. So
\alpha \amp= (-\sin t)(-\sin t\,dt)+(\cos t)(\cos t\,dt) \amp= dt.
Therefore \boxed{\int_C\alpha=2\pi.}

subsection.md:
\boxed{\begin{array}{c}
\text{finite piecewise smooth geometry is allowed,}\\[1mm]
\text{but jumps, singularities, and wild boundaries are not covered by the basic theorem.}
\end{array}}
